# 🔒 AWS EC2 Security Best Practices

A comprehensive guide to securing your AWS EC2 instances and infrastructure.

---

## 🚫 Root Account Protection

- **Disable root access** – Only use the root account to create your first IAM user
- **Enable MFA on root account** – Add an extra layer of security to your most privileged account

---

## 🎯 Least Privilege Principle

Grant only the minimum permissions necessary for users to perform their tasks. Never grant excessive permissions.

---

## 👤 IAM Roles & Policies

- Use **IAM roles** for application access to AWS resources
- **Regularly rotate access keys** – Update credentials frequently to minimize exposure risk
- Review and audit IAM policies monthly

---

## 🌐 VPC Security

- **Security Groups & Network ACLs** – Strictly control inbound and outbound traffic
- **Private Subnets** – Deploy instances in private subnets whenever possible
- Use bastion hosts for SSH access to private instances

---

## 🛡️ Instance Security

- **Keep systems updated** – Regularly patch and update your instances
- **Host-based firewalls** – Implement additional firewall protection at the instance level
- Disable unnecessary services and ports

---

## 📊 Logging & Monitoring

| Service | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **AWS CloudTrail** | Audit and log all API calls for compliance |
| **Amazon CloudWatch** | Monitor instance performance and security metrics |
| **VPC Flow Logs** | Track network traffic for security analysis |

---

## 🔐 Data Protection

- **Encryption at rest** – Use AWS KMS to encrypt stored data
- **Encryption in transit** – Protect data moving between services with TLS/SSL
- Manage encryption keys securely in AWS Secrets Manager

---

## 💾 Backup & Recovery

- **Automated EBS Snapshots** – Implement regular, automated backups
- **Multi-region backups** – Store backups in different regions for disaster recovery
- Test recovery procedures regularly

---

## 🚨 Incident Response

- Develop a comprehensive incident response plan
- Regularly test and update your response procedures
- Document all security incidents and responses

---

## ✅ Compliance

Ensure your infrastructure complies with:
- **GDPR** – General Data Protection Regulation
- **HIPAA** – Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act
- **SOC 2** – Service Organization Control
- Industry-specific regulations relevant to your business

---

## 📋 Security Checklist

- [ ] Enable CloudTrail logging
- [ ] Apply the principle of least privilege
- [ ] Regularly patch and update instances
- [ ] Enable multi-factor authentication (MFA)
- [ ] Review IAM roles and permissions monthly
- [ ] Set up CloudWatch alarms for suspicious activity
- [ ] Implement VPC Flow Logs
- [ ] Test disaster recovery procedures
- [ ] Document all security policies
- [ ] Conduct security audits quarterly

